This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with 3D object recognition using point cloud-based learning frameworks. It also involves the use of nonlinear activation layers, which are commonly used in computer vision tasks. 

The paper also involves the optimization of kernel distribution and its receptive field, which falls under the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). 

The use of Radial Basis Functions (RBF) is a common technique in Neural Networks (cs.NE), which is another likely sub-category for this paper. 

Finally, the paper involves modeling the spatial distribution of point clouds, which falls under the sub-category of Graphics (cs.GR).
